I sing beneath the brightening skies,
With joy that knows no end,
Each bird and beast, their wild reprise,
Through boundless nature, blend.

For every breath becomes a prayer,
In harmony, we soar,
As life weaves tales beyond compare,
In nature's endless lore.


- Henry David Thoreau
